<div id="review_2153392338" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2153392338" />
    <a title="Amanda Littlefair" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62783056-amanda-littlefair"><img alt="Amanda Littlefair" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1516647533p2/62783056.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2153392338?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amanda Littlefair" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amanda Littlefair" href="/user/show/62783056-amanda-littlefair">Amanda Littlefair</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2153392338" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5605941022336298189">I&apos;m really hoping for a release of a 3rd and improved volume - not reading about it anywhere and it&apos;s been 6 years since this one has published.<br/><br/>The format of the translated version was a little distracting at points (specifically where dialect-heavy) which would draw me out of the story or interrupt the flow. A little bit frustrating, especially when you have a few pages of seamless reading and then it pops up again. I didn&apos;t find this problem so much with the first book. I&apos;m hoping a new editor</span>
  <span id="freeText5605941022336298189" style="display:none">I'm really hoping for a release of a 3rd and improved volume - not reading about it anywhere and it's been 6 years since this one has published.<br /><br />The format of the translated version was a little distracting at points (specifically where dialect-heavy) which would draw me out of the story or interrupt the flow. A little bit frustrating, especially when you have a few pages of seamless reading and then it pops up again. I didn't find this problem so much with the first book. I'm hoping a new editor is hired if Eva writes the third volume.<br /><br />I appreciate that the chapters are short, it doesn't feel like reading near 400 pages.<br /><br />Some points did drag a little bit, but the ending had me sitting upright. When I get excited, my eyes flit around the page so I had to cover the passages I wasn't up to yet to prevent spoiling things for myself haha. <br /><br />**SPOILER ALERT**<br />Maybe it's because I'm a sucker for drama but I really enjoyed the setup for Adriana and Gunnarr in the end. I'm hoping to see more of this suspected love triangle rear its head with aaaaall the impractical romantics.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5605941022336298189" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


