<span id="freeTextContainer12753654409281279055">I had been really looking forward to the second book in the Immortal Collection as I like the way Eva portrays her characters, conveying their ancient wisdom but also their capacity to still make the most basic human errors time &amp; time &amp; time again. <br/><br/>The saga is stuffed full of facts about ancient cultures as the Longevos are involved in some of the most famous episodes in human history. <br/><br/>The story didn&apos;t disappoint and though it was paced much faster than the 1st book, it was satisfying finding o</span>
  <span id="freeText12753654409281279055" style="display:none">I had been really looking forward to the second book in the Immortal Collection as I like the way Eva portrays her characters, conveying their ancient wisdom but also their capacity to still make the most basic human errors time &amp; time &amp; time again. <br /><br />The saga is stuffed full of facts about ancient cultures as the Longevos are involved in some of the most famous episodes in human history. <br /><br />The story didn't disappoint and though it was paced much faster than the 1st book, it was satisfying finding out the back stories of the family and Mother. <br /><br />Sadly I have had to mark this book down 1 star as it was seriously marred by a lot of translation errors, which were really irritating. There were contradictions in the same sentence and some really basic errors as if a Google translate had been used and not a human translator, very sloppy editing. What a shame. <br /><br />Eva please can you make sure that the next book is translated properly. Thank you so much. And I am really looking forward to reading the 3rd book. xx</span>
