        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1631263816" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17608393890153238909"><strong>Disappointed</strong><br/><br/>First of all, I gave the first book five stars. This, the second in the series, was such a departure from the original. It was about half the length of the first, the translation was full of errors, some of them cataclysmic, like saying someone wasn&apos;t in the room, then suddenly they are talking, weird stuff like that, switching character names, numerous typos, wrong pronouns used, just generally error prone. It was odd, but worst of all was the story. It just seemed mixed up, the cha</span>
  <span id="freeText17608393890153238909" style="display:none"><strong>Disappointed</strong><br /><br />First of all, I gave the first book five stars. This, the second in the series, was such a departure from the original. It was about half the length of the first, the translation was full of errors, some of them cataclysmic, like saying someone wasn't in the room, then suddenly they are talking, weird stuff like that, switching character names, numerous typos, wrong pronouns used, just generally error prone. It was odd, but worst of all was the story. It just seemed mixed up, the characters were so inconsistent, terribly wishy-washy in fact. I didn't like this story and leaving it with this cliff hanger that there is a war coming in the next book doesn't even interest me in the next book. I think I'm done with this series. Sorry about it too, really grew interested in them in book one, but with Lyra dead, Lur is really the only one left that's even likeable.</span>
