<div id="review_1611686881" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1611686881" />
    <a title="Eboni Lindsey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49283877-eboni-lindsey"><img alt="Eboni Lindsey" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1611686881?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eboni Lindsey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eboni Lindsey" href="/user/show/49283877-eboni-lindsey">Eboni Lindsey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/22825351-the-sons-of-adam">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1611686881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12573203403050213446"><strong>Yes there are grammatical errors...</strong><br/><br/>So there are some grammatical errors in the translation edition of the sons of Adam, but that shouldn&apos;t dissuade a fan of the first book. The book goes on an intriguing ride from the devastating ice age to the first settlers of America, to the last moments of Pompeii to the age of Vikings. It is an intricate web full of fury, revenge, and, most of all, love. I highly recommend this book, grammatical errors and all, but the errors aren&apos;t as in your face and comp</span>
  <span id="freeText12573203403050213446" style="display:none"><strong>Yes there are grammatical errors...</strong><br /><br />So there are some grammatical errors in the translation edition of the sons of Adam, but that shouldn't dissuade a fan of the first book. The book goes on an intriguing ride from the devastating ice age to the first settlers of America, to the last moments of Pompeii to the age of Vikings. It is an intricate web full of fury, revenge, and, most of all, love. I highly recommend this book, grammatical errors and all, but the errors aren't as in your face and completely indecipherable as some may think, so give the book a chance, it will definitely have you wanting to read the next book as soon as it comes out!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12573203403050213446" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


